modules.description: Converts between camelCase, snake_case, and kebab-case strings using precise transformation functions. Operates on strings and provides methods to detect and convert case formats. Useful for normalizing identifiers in code generation or data processing pipelines.

Converts strings between various naming conventions, including splitting camel, snake, and kebab cases into individual words, and transforming between upper/lower camel case, snake case, kebab case, HTTP headers, and constant case. Operates on single strings, applying pattern recognition and transformation rules to reformat identifiers. Used for normalizing API parameters, generating consistent variable names, and preparing data for external systems with specific casing requirements.
